import java.util.* ;
import java.io.*; 
public class Solution {
    public static int ninjaAndTriangle(int n) {
        int low = 1 , high = n, ans = 0;
        while(low <= high){
            int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;
            long sum = (long)mid * (mid + 1)/2;

            if(sum <= n){
                ans = mid;
                low = mid + 1;
            }else{
                high = mid - 1;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
Ninja has been given ‘N’ stars. Ninja has to make a triangle using these stars. The ‘i’th’ level of a triangle contains a ‘i’ number of stars.
Can you help Ninja to make a triangle as large as possible using these stars?

If the number of stars is 7 in the above example, then also the maximum height of the triangle is 3. This is because to make a triangle of heigh
